'''Bassorah Fossa''' is a [[Trough (geology)|trough]] south of [[Ali Baba (crater)|Ali Baba]] [[impact crater|crater]] on [[Saturn]]'s moon [[Enceladus (moon)|Enceladus]].  Bassorah Fossa was first seen in ''[[Voyager 2]]'' images.  It is located at 45.4° [[north]], 6.3° west, and is 131 kilometers long.

Bassorah Fossa is named after the city of [[Basra]], [[Iraq]], from which [[Sindbad]] embarked on his third voyage in the ''[[Arabian Nights]]''.{{fact|date=April 2013}}

