{{wiktionary}}
'''Dynamicism''', also termed the ''dynamic hypothesis'' or the ''dynamic hypothesis in cognitive science'' or ''dynamic cognition'', is a new approach in [[cognitive science]] exemplified by the work of philosopher [[Tim van Gelder]]. It argues that [[differential equations]] are more suited to modeling [[cognition]] than more traditional [[computer]] models. Cf also [[dynamical systems theory]].

