[[File:Ossian-Aschan-1922.jpg|thumb|right|Ossian Aschan in 1922.]]
'''Adolf Ossian Aschan''' (16 May 1860, [[Helsinki]] – 25 February 1939) was a [[Finland|Finnish]] chemist and politician. He was a member of the [[Parliament of Finland]] from 1910 to 1911, representing the [[Swedish People's Party of Finland]] (SFP).<ref>[http://www.eduskunta.fi/ Eduskunta.]</ref> He served as the professor of chemistry at the [[University of Helsinki]] from 1908 to 1927.

