'''''Teknisk Ukeblad''''' (TU, {{lang-en|Technical Weekly Magazine}}) is a [[Norway|Norwegian]] engineering magazine.
''TU'' has appeared weekly since 13 April 1883 and was published by Ingeniørforlaget, now Teknisk Ukeblad Media jointly owned by three national professional associations of engineers and architects: the [[Norwegian Society of Engineers and Technologists]] (NITO, founded 1936), [[Tekna (association)|Tekna]] (founded in 1874), and the [[Norwegian Polytechnic Society]] (PF, founded 1852).
On 24 June 2010 ''TU'' had a total circulation of 302,000 weekly copies.
Corresponding publications are ''[[Ny Teknik]]'' in Sweden<ref name=ne>{{cite encyclopedia | title=Ny Teknik | encyclopedia=[[Nationalencyklopedin]] | url=http://www.ne.se/ny-teknik | language=Swedish | accessdate=11 September 2010}} {{Subscription required}}</ref>, ''[[Ingeniøren]]'' in Denmark and ''[[Technisch Weekblad]]'' in the [[Netherlands]].
